        <h2>Algorithm idea</h2>
        <div class="description">
          <p>Similar to BFS, Depth-First Search (DFS) is an uninformed search algorithm that explores as far as possible along each branch before backtracking.  </p>
          <p>At each step, DFS moves to an unvisited neighbor of the current node.</p>
          <p>If it reaches a node with no unvisited neighbors, it backtracks to the previous node to explore a different branch. DFS uses a Last-In-First-Out (LIFO) stack to manage the frontier.</p>
        </div>
